******
[6] Maine (Waldo County)
Date: Fri 8 Apr 2022
Source: Fox Bangor [edited]
https://www.foxbangor.com/news/item/bird-flu-cases-continue-to-spread/


The bird flu is spreading through Maine with another case reported, this time in a new county. Officials said this latest report is in Waldo County and involves 47 birds from a backyard mixed species.

It is now the 12th case in the state, with nearly 900 birds killed as a result.

The state says migratory birds are the culprits for spreading the virus, making it a real challenge for the state to control it.

Officials say they are depending on bird owners to help. They say the best way to protect your flock is to keep them inside.

If you do see dead birds, contact the state as that is an indicator of the virus.

Experts say warmer months should help the avian flu to subside, but it will likely return in the fall.

